        <property propertyId="67f102e2-9cb6-4d20-aa16-bf74d8a03326" amount="1.0" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">wet mass</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. Global demand of paint is estimated to be 45600000000kg (http://www.freedoniagroup.com/brochure/28xx/2845smwe.pdf, accessed 20151009) of which 55% is paint and 35% is emulsion paint (http://www.psgdover.com/en/mouvex-paint-coatings-market-overview/what-are-paint-a-coatings/defining-paintaccessed, accessed 20151009). 22% is considered hazardous waste and 78% non hazardous waste (http://archive.epa.gov/sectors/web/pdf/paint_quantity_report.pdf, accessed 20151009). In the US, of hazardous waste 7.2% is sent to hazardous incineration (http://www3.epa.gov/epawaste/hazard/tsd/td/combustion.htm, accessed 20151009). Of non hazardous waste 12% is sent to incineration (Extrapolated from the US data, according to GDP. The relative GDP of US in 2005 was .274857, compared to the global value of 1. EPA estimates that 12% of annual MSW in US is incinerated for energy recovery http://www.epa.gov/epawaste/nonhaz/municipal/pubs/2012_msw_fs.pdf) 23% is sent to inert material landfill (http://archive.epa.gov/sectors/web/pdf/paint_quantity_report.pdf, accessed 20151009). The rest (65%) is considered to go to sanitary landfill. In the EU (from Eurostat municipal waste treatment http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/web/waste/transboundary-waste-shipments/key-waste-streams/municipal-waste), of hazardous waste 23% is sent to hazardous incineration. Of non hazardous waste 23% is sent to incineration. 37% is considered to be sent to landfilling and it is split between sanitary and inert landfill using the same shares assumed for the US. The treatment activities for the global dataset are calculated as the weighted average of US and EU, based on nominal GDP of 2010 (source: United Nations, http://data.un.org/Glossary.aspx?q=GDP+%28current+US%24%29, accessed 20130726 and 20130312). Where EU without CH GDP is 2.80E-01 and US is 0.253094 of the world. Gross domestic product (GDP) at current prices is GDP at prices of the current reporting period. Also known as nominal GDP. The assumed treatment are 16% of hazardous waste goes to incineration. For non hazardous, 20% goes to incineration, 12% goes to inert landfill, and 56% goes to sanitary landfill.</productionVolumeComment>
